<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="976" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d976">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16124a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                                interests in Mexico</hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>41. Telegraph brief statement regarding present conditions Mexico City,
                            number Americans that have left since arrival Gonzalez, present status
                            railway communication with Vera Cruz, and probable number Americans who
                            will leave in immediate future; also whether attitude American colony
                            toward you is friendly or otherwise.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>